cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on understanding and modeling the linguistic strategies used in interpreting verbal irony. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories as the paper discusses the design of computational models to capture these strategies. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper touches on the social and cultural aspects of human communication involving verbal irony. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly focus on the acoustic properties of verbal irony.
